mathphrase
Element


mathphrase
&mathphrase.purpose;


&mathphrase.synopsis.gen;
Description


A mathphrase is a simple, inline equation, one that
can be represented using ordinary text, symbols, subscripts, and
superscripts. 
E=mc2,
for example.


Processing expectations

&format.inline;



&mathphrase.parents.gen;
&mathphrase.children.gen;



